nmsEAPSRings.name: nmsEAPSRings
nmsEAPSRings.description: The number of running ethernet ring instances.

nmsEAPSPduRx.name: nmsEAPSPduRx
nmsEAPSPduRx.description: The total number of input EAPS PDUs.

nmsEAPSPduTx.name: nmsEAPSPduTx
nmsEAPSPduTx.description: The total number of output EAPS PDUs.

nmsEAPSRingTable.name: nmsEAPSRingTable
nmsEAPSRingTable.description: A table that contains information of ethernet ring instances.

nmsEAPSRingTableEntry.name: nmsEAPSRingTableEntry
nmsEAPSRingTableEntry.description: A table that contains information of ethernet ring instances.

nmsEAPSRingID.name: nmsEAPSRingID
nmsEAPSRingID.description: The index of ethernet ring instances.

nmsEAPSRingNodeType.name: nmsEAPSRingNodeType
nmsEAPSRingNodeType.description: A value indicates the node-type of this device in the ring.

nmsEAPSRingControlVlan.name: nmsEAPSRingControlVlan
nmsEAPSRingControlVlan.description: The id of the VLAN in which EAPS PDUs are transmitted.

nmsEAPSRingPorts.name: nmsEAPSRingPorts
nmsEAPSRingPorts.description: The number of interfaces which are configured in a ring.

nmsEAPSRingState.name: nmsEAPSRingState
nmsEAPSRingState.description: A value indicates the state of a node in the ring. Only the value from a MasterNode indicates the state of the whole ring. The value from a TransitNode means the local ring ports are all operational or not.

nmsEAPSRingHealthCheck.name: nmsEAPSRingHealthCheck
nmsEAPSRingHealthCheck.description: A value indicates whether Health packets are being sent from MasterNode. Available only for MasterNodes.

nmsEAPSRingHelloTime.name: nmsEAPSRingHelloTime
nmsEAPSRingHelloTime.description: The inteval between the transmit of two Health packets, in seconds. Available only for MasterNodes.

nmsEAPSRingFailTime.name: nmsEAPSRingFailTime
nmsEAPSRingFailTime.description: The hold time for the SecondaryPort after a Health packet is received, in seconds. Available only for MasterNodes.

nmsEAPSRingPreforwardTime.name: nmsEAPSRingPreforwardTime
nmsEAPSRingPreforwardTime.description: The hold time for a TransitPort which is recovered from a failure, in seconds. During the pre-forward time, no packets other than PDUs in control vlan can be forwarded. Only available for TransitNodes.

nmsEAPSRingAdminStatus.name: nmsEAPSRingAdminStatus
nmsEAPSRingAdminStatus.description: A read-create value that indicates the configuration status of the ring instance. Set this value to 'enabled' to start the ring or 'disabled' to stop it. The value 'running' indicates that the ring is currently configured and running, in which case, the values of node-type and control-vlan cannot be modified.

nmsEAPSRingPrimaryPort.name: nmsEAPSRingPrimaryPort
nmsEAPSRingPrimaryPort.description: The interface index of the primary-port if the 'nmsEAPSRingNodeType' is 'masterNode', or the ifIndex of the first transit-port if 'transitNode'. Value 0 means that this port is not configured.

nmsEAPSRingPrimaryPortState.name: nmsEAPSRingPrimaryPortState
nmsEAPSRingPrimaryPortState.description: The forwarding state of the primary-port or the first transit-port.

nmsEAPSRingPrimaryPortStatus.name: nmsEAPSRingPrimaryPortStatus
nmsEAPSRingPrimaryPortStatus.description: The link status of the primary-port or the first transit-port.

nmsEAPSRingSecondaryPort.name: nmsEAPSRingSecondaryPort
nmsEAPSRingSecondaryPort.description: The interface index of the secondary-port if the 'nmsEAPSRingNodeType' is 'masterNode', or the ifIndex of the second transit-port if 'transitNode'. Value 0 means that this port is not configured.

nmsEAPSRingSecondaryPortState.name: nmsEAPSRingSecondaryPortState
nmsEAPSRingSecondaryPortState.description: The forwarding state of the secondary-port or the second transit-port.

nmsEAPSRingSecondaryPortStatus.name: nmsEAPSRingSecondaryPortStatus
nmsEAPSRingSecondaryPortStatus.description: The link status of the secondary-port or the second transit-port.

nmsEAPSRingPortTable.name: nmsEAPSRingPortTable
nmsEAPSRingPortTable.description: A table that contains information of ethernet ring ports.

nmsEAPSRingPortTableEntry.name: nmsEAPSRingPortTableEntry
nmsEAPSRingPortTableEntry.description: A table that contains information of ethernet ring ports.

nmsEAPSRingPortRingID.name: nmsEAPSRingPortRingID
nmsEAPSRingPortRingID.description: The index of an ethernet ring instance, in which this port is configured.

nmsEAPSRingPort.name: nmsEAPSRingPort
nmsEAPSRingPort.description: The port number of the ring port.

nmsEAPSRingPortType.name: nmsEAPSRingPortType
nmsEAPSRingPortType.description: A value indicates the type of a ring port.

nmsEAPSRingPortState.name: nmsEAPSRingPortState
nmsEAPSRingPortState.description: A value indicates the forward state of a ring port in data vlans.

nmsEAPSRingPortForwards.name: nmsEAPSRingPortForwards
nmsEAPSRingPortForwards.description: The number of times this port has transitioned to forwarding state.

nmsEAPSRingPortRx.name: nmsEAPSRingPortRx
nmsEAPSRingPortRx.description: The number of received EAPS PDUs on this port.

nmsEAPSRingPortTx.name: nmsEAPSRingPortTx
nmsEAPSRingPortTx.description: The Number of transmitted EAPS PDUs on this port.

nmsEAPSRingPortStatus.name: nmsEAPSRingPortStatus
nmsEAPSRingPortStatus.description: The link status of the ring port.

nmsEAPSRingNotification.name: nmsEAPSRingNotification
nmsEAPSRingNotification.description: This notification is generated when a MasterNode detects that the state of ring is changed.
